timeline.bodyText:
This code looks like a repetition of the method
private void updateAttributes(Feature selectedFeature)

in the controller class.
Not too sure if it's good practice, but you could modify the signature to:
static void updateAttributes(Feature selectedFeature)

By leaving out private and making it static, it would be 'protected', meaning available to this dialog class, and it being 'static' would allow you to import it into this file as a static import:
import static com.esri.samples.edit_features_with_feature_linked_annotation.EditFeaturesWithFeatureLinkedAnnotationController.updateAttributes;

And then you could replace the whole ListenableFuture block here with simply:
          // update feature in the feature table
          updateAttributes(selectedFeature);

Like I said, not sure whether this is good practice.
@colinanderson could you advise whether this is considered SOLID?
But before you go through the effort of doing this, I suppose we'd need @Rachael-E 's input whether this is user-friendly enough...

